  "body": "# submission name:\r\nqpose14\r\n\r\n# upload zipped `archive.zip`\r\n[archive.zip](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/27206870/archive.zip)\r\n\r\n# report.txt\r\n<!-- do not check it in the code (it's already ignored in .gitignore) -->\r\n<!-- copy the report.txt content here -->\r\n```\r\n === Evaluation config ===\r\n   batch_size: 16\r\n   device: cuda\r\n   num_threads: 2\r\n   prefetch_queue_depth: 4\r\n   report: submissions/qpose14/report.txt\r\n   seed: 1234\r\n   submission_dir: submissions/qpose14\r\n   uncompressed_dir: /content/comma_video_compression_challenge/videos\r\n   video_names_file: /content/comma_video_compression_challenge/public_test_video_names.txt\r\n === Evaluation results over 600 samples ===\r\n   Average PoseNet Distortion: 0.00052154\r\n   Average SegNet Distortion: 0.00061261\r\n   Submission file size: 287,573 bytes\r\n   Original uncompressed size: 37,545,489 bytes\r\n   Compression Rate: 0.00765932\r\n   Final score: 100segnet_dist + √(10posenet_dist) + 25*rate = 0.32\r\n```\r\n\r\n# does your submission require gpu for evaluation (inflation)?\r\nyes\r\n\r\n# did you include the compression script? and want it to be merged?\r\nno\r\n\r\n# additional comments\r\nqpose14 is a rate-optimized Quantizr-style neural renderer variant. The improvement is a quantized pose side-channel plus single-member archive packing to reduce zip overhead. Validated on CUDA using Google Colab.\r\n",
